article.headline: UC Santa Barbara 67, Pacific 57
article.story: SANTA BARBARA, Calif. -- Chris Devine had 26 points and eight rebounds Wednesday night to lead UC Santa Barbara to its first three-game winning streak of the season with a 67-57 victory over Pacific. Devine went 8-for-15 from the field and made all 10 of his free throws for the Gauchos (11-13, 5-7 Big West Conference). Chad Troyer sank a trio of 3-pointers in the first five minutes as Pacific (14-10, 7-6) took an 11-5 lead. But James Powell scored 10 of his 16 points in an eight-minute run as Santa Barbara surged to a 36-27 halftime lead. The Tigers got as close as seven points on a dunk by Sam Willard with 16:44 to go, but Devine's two baskets keyed an 8-2 run that put the Gauchos back on course. UC Santa Barbara its last 13 points from the foul line in 14 attempts. Troyer finished with 11 to lead Pacific.
